According to a 2024 Gallup study on remote and hybrid work trends, 52% of U.S. employees whose jobs can be done remotely work in a hybrid environment, while 27% are fully remote. Fully remote workers report the highest engagement (31%) compared to hybrid (23%) and on-site workers (19%). However, some studies indicate productivity actually drops when working fully remotely. A Stanford analysis of existing studies shows that fully remote workers' productivity dropped between 10% and 20%. Despite this, 77% of workers believe they are more productive when working remotely, highlighting a gap between employee perception and some academic findings.
